messages.content: Is someone from team able to give a TLDR on this update? Want to do x post promoting it but need some ELI5 if anyone can...  Hows this helping holders? Or is it purely fixing mining issues?

In a nutshell:
- We’re moving to share based evaluations instead of pure hash rate. 
- Adds support for high difficulty miners. This was a bottleneck which didn’t allow high powered machines to participate in the network. 
- Adds support for solo mining & other pools instead of only Braiins. This is a big one. 
- We added 2 proxy implementations, lightweight one for miners and batteries included for validators (although miners can also the full one with some tweaks). This open source proxy is probably the only one which is built with latest tech, previous open source implementations are very old (~10 years). 
- Dashboards are included to see real time stats along with full share accounting. 
- Adds the groundwork for miners to earn BTC as well, with inspiration from TIDES framework. This is the next step. 
- Also now we won’t depend on third-party services to help us evaluate miners; we can do it on our own and tweak it as we want moving forward.

 Miners send hashpower to a shared pool
 Validators measure each miner’s contribution
 Rewards scale with validator stake
 TAOHash sells rewards and buys back Alpha to support price

 Promotes decentralization across mining and rewards

This week, we’re shipping a big upgrade to Subnet 14 — this upgrade will start paying BTC rewards directly to Miners. All Miners will simply publish their BTC payout addresses and we'll coordinate payouts. This means miners will get 97.5% of their mined BTC back in BTC and ~0.5% in Alpha (i.e. the subnet nets ~2% of the BTC value while taking 2.5% of the BTC mined).

This also means we're switching to a centralized pool model to facilitate this. This means a Validator update is coming shortly, and it also means that the mining overhead will be reduced!

As for the roadmap, in around 2 weeks we'll be adding support for the TIDES share valuation algorithm which will allow us to move to our own pool software even as we scale-up hashrate. It will mean BTC payments to miners will happen less frequently until we scale hashrate up, so the BTC-portion will be paid out when we hit a block, accounting for shares produced up until the block mined. However, miners will consistently get their Alpha rewards. More on this closer to release!

Lastly, we have a smart contract write in-progress to allow the subnet to operate like a decentralized hashrate rental market. This will allow more frequent payouts to the miners as bidders purchase hashrate and will increase the revenue that the subnet receives.

Thanks for bearing with us. Mine on!
